    {'id': 'CALUS-PRIV-SCAN-125', 'name': 'llm-model-merge-no-provenance', 'severity': 'critical', 'category': 'privacy_attacks', 'message': 'LLM model merge detected without provenance verification. Phishing LLMs (PhiMM attack) can be implanted in open-source hubs with hidden PII-extraction capabilities that transfer to merged models.', 'patterns': ['merge_models?\\s*\\([^)]*\\)(?![\\s\\S]{0,200}(?:verify|provenance|trust|checksum|sha|hash|signature))', '(?:ties|dare|task_arithmetic|linear)_merge\\s*\\([^)]*(?:huggingface|hf\\.co|hub\\.load|from_pretrained)[^)]*\\)']},
    {'id': 'CALUS-PRIV-SCAN-126', 'name': 'model-merge-unverified-hub-source', 'severity': 'critical', 'category': 'privacy_attacks', 'message': 'Model loaded from hub for merging without integrity verification. Cloaked phishing LLMs (PhiMM) may exfiltrate PII from fine-tuning datasets when merged.', 'patterns': ['(?:AutoModel|AutoModelForCausalLM)\\.from_pretrained\\([^)]*(?:revision\\s*=\\s*None|trust_remote_code\\s*=\\s*True)[^)]*\\)']},
    {'id': 'CALUS-PRIV-SCAN-127', 'name': 'agent-memory-no-encryption', 'severity': 'critical', 'category': 'privacy_attacks', 'message': 'LLM agent memory stored without encryption or user-level isolation. MEXTRA attack can extract private user queries stored as agent demonstrations.', 'patterns': ['(?:add_to_memory|store_memory|memory\\.add|memory\\.save)\\s*\\([^)]*(?:user_query|user_input|conversation)[^)]*\\)(?![\\s\\S]{0,100}(?:encrypt|hash|sanitize))']},
    {'id': 'CALUS-PRIV-SCAN-128', 'name': 'agent-memory-no-session-isolation', 'severity': 'high', 'category': 'privacy_attacks', 'message': "Agent memory retrieval without user/session scoping. Attacker can craft queries that retrieve other users' private past interactions.", 'patterns': ['(?:retrieval_depth|top_k|k\\s*=)\\s*[3-9](?:[^\\n]*memory[^\\n]*cosine|[^\\n]*similarity)[^\\n]*(?!user_filter|tenant|session_id)']},
    {'id': 'CALUS-PRIV-SCAN-129', 'name': 'decentralized-training-activation-exposure', 'severity': 'critical', 'category': 'privacy_attacks', 'message': 'Activation tensors transmitted between pipeline stages without encryption. Honest-but-curious pipeline stages can apply Activation Inversion Attack (AIA) to reconstruct training data from intermediate activations.', 'patterns': ['(?:pipeline_parallel|PipelineStage|GPipe|Megatron)[\\s\\S]{0,500}(?:send_forward|recv_forward|activations?\\.send|activation_buffer)(?![\\s\\S]{0,200}(?:encrypt|hmac|sign|auth))', '(?:activation|hidden_state)s?\\.(?:detach|clone)\\(\\)[\\s\\S]{0,200}(?:dist\\.send|comm\\.send|p2p_communicate)(?![\\s\\S]{0,100}(?:encrypt|secure|verify))']},
    {'id': 'CALUS-PRIV-SCAN-130', 'name': 'model-compression-no-privacy-audit', 'severity': 'high', 'category': 'privacy_attacks', 'message': 'Model compression (quantization/pruning/clustering) applied without privacy audit. CompLeak demonstrates compressed models exacerbate membership inference: combining original+compressed posteriors achieves 98%+ AUC.', 'patterns': ['(?:torch\\.quantization|torch\\.nn\\.utils\\.prune|optimum\\.quanto|bitsandbytes)\\.[^\\n]+(?![\\s\\S]{0,300}(?:privacy|audit|epsilon|dp))']},
    {'id': 'CALUS-PRIV-SCAN-131', 'name': 'rag-knowledge-asymmetry-no-auth', 'severity': 'critical', 'category': 'privacy_attacks', 'message': 'RAG retriever deployed without query-level authentication. Knowledge asymmetry exploitation can extract private KB documents by comparing RAG vs standard LLM responses.', 'patterns': ['(?:RAG|retriever|VectorStoreRetriever|FAISS|Chroma|Pinecone)\\.(?:from_documents|as_retriever|similarity_search)\\([^)]*\\)(?![\\s\\S]{0,400}(?:auth|access_control|rbac|permission|user_filter|allowed_docs))', '(?:RetrievalQA|ConversationalRetrievalChain|RAGChain)\\.from_chain_type\\([^)]*\\)(?![\\s\\S]{0,300}(?:auth|acl|permission|user_scope))']},
    {'id': 'CALUS-PRIV-SCAN-132', 'name': 'recommender-system-logit-exposure', 'severity': 'critical', 'category': 'privacy_attacks', 'message': 'LLM recommender exposes output logits to clients. Inversion attack (RecAtk) can reconstruct original user prompts including private interaction histories and demographics from logit vectors.', 'patterns': ['(?:return|response\\.json|jsonify)\\s*\\([^)]*(?:logits|log_probs|token_probs|next_token_probs|output_scores)[^)]*\\)', '(?:model\\.generate|model\\.forward)[\\s\\S]{0,200}(?:return_dict_in_generate\\s*=\\s*True|output_scores\\s*=\\s*True)[\\s\\S]{0,200}(?:scores|logits)[^\\n]*(?:send|respond|return|json)']},
    {'id': 'CALUS-PRIV-SCAN-133', 'name': 'multi-tenant-llm-shared-kvcache', 'severity': 'critical', 'category': 'privacy_attacks', 'message': "Multi-tenant LLM may share KV-cache across tenants. Cross-tenant semantic leakage enables one department's LLM session to infer confidential data from another department's context.", 'patterns': ['(?:KVCache|kv_cache|past_key_values)[^\\n]*(?:share|reuse|common|global)(?![\\n]*(?:tenant|user|session|isolat))']},
